Central America
---
Nicaragua (national). 29 Mar 2016. (reported) 129 cases, 3 in past 24 hours, of whom 14 are pregnant women.
http://spanish.people.com.cn/n3/2016/0329/c31614-9037003.html [in Spanish]

Caribbean
---
Cuba (national). 24 Mar 2016. (conf.) 32-year-old pregnant health worker ex Venezuela; 6th imported case.
http://en.granma.cu/cuba/2016-03-24/sixth-imported-case-of-zika-virus-confirmed

[Cuba has vector mosquitoes transmitting dengue viruses, so these imported cases pose a risk of ongoing transmission of Zika virus. - Mod.TY]

Martinique (national). 25 Mar 2016. (reported) 14 320 cases; 1 case of microcephaly; mother confirmed as Zika virus infected early in pregnancy, fetus with brain calcifications similar to cases reported in French Polynesia and Brazil. Atrophy of the corpus callosum (brain structure connecting the 2 hemispheres) is also visible on ultrasound. Guillain-Barré syndrome [GBS] in 5 patients with confirmed post-Zika virus infection and 4 additional GBS cases under investigation.
http://www.pourquoidocteur.fr/Articles/Question-d-actu/14819-Zika-les-autorites-confirment-le-1er-cas-de-microcephalie-en-Martinique [in French, trans. Corr.SB]

French Guiana (national). 25 Mar 2016. (reported) 2770 cases of whom 74 are pregnant women; Guillain-Barré syndrome in 2 patients with confirmed post-Zika virus infections.
http://www.franceguyane.mobi/actualite/education-sante-environnement/le-zika-en-hausse-sur-le-littoral-286475.php [in French, trans. Corr.SB]

Guadeloupe (national). 25 Mar 2016. (susp.) 794, (conf.) 134 cases, among whom 2 pregnant women; Myelitis 1 teen-aged girl [Zika virus infection status not given]
http://www.pourquoidocteur.fr/Articles/Question-d-actu/14819-Zika-les-autorites-confirment-le-1er-cas-de-microcephalie-en-Martinique [in French, trans. Corr.SB]

St Martin (national). 25 Mar 2016. (conf.) 154 cases, (conf.) 30 cases of whom 1 is a pregnant woman.
http://www.pourquoidocteur.fr/Articles/Question-d-actu/14819-Zika-les-autorites-confirment-le-1er-cas-de-microcephalie-en-Martinique [in French, trans. Corr.SB]

Puerto Rico (national). 28 Mar 2016. (reported) 350 cases of whom 40 are pregnant women; 100 cases in past week; Guillain-Barré syndrome, 3 cases [but no mention if they had a prior Zika virus infection. - Mod.TY]
http://www.news4jax.com/web/wjxt/news/international/puerto-rico-sees-rise-in-zika-cases-paralyzing-condition

South America
---
Argentina (national). 29 Mar 2016. (conf. and probable) as of 19 Mar 2016, 780 cases; 1 case locally acquired in Cordoba province; 16 cases imported, diagnosed in Ciudad de Buenos Aires, Buenos Aires, Córdoba, Mendoza, Corrientes, and Chubut.
http://www.telam.com.ar/notas/201603/141210-dengue-argentina.html [in Spanish]

Colombia (national). 29 Mar 2016. As of week 11 [week of 18 Mar 2016], (susp.) 56 477 cases, (conf.) 2361 cases, including 997 pregnant women. Another 9815 pregnant women with symptoms compatible with Zika virus infection. 50 microcephalic babies, of which 18 negative and 32 still under investigation. 258 cases of Guillain-Barré syndrome associated with Zika virus infection of 381 neurological syndromes reported.
http://www.radiosantafe.com/2016/03/29/34-nacidos-vivos-con-microcefalia-investiga-el-ins-en-colombia/ [in Spanish]

Countries with cases but no ongoing transmission
---
Canada (national). 25 Mar 2016. (reported) 32 cases, one of whom is a woman in Saskatchewan province with suspected sexual transmission.
http://ici.radio-canada.ca/nouvelles/sante/2016/03/24/001-zika-sante-werker-publique-saskatchewan-transmission-sexuelle-canada.shtml [in French, trans. Corr.SB]

Spain (national). 29 Mar 2016. (conf.) 58 cases imported from Zika virus affected countries.
http://pulse.ng/health/zika-virus-58-cases-confirmed-in-spain-id4856706.html

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Spain can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4129524,43. - Mod.TY]

